New package – a dedicated @ghatana/artifact-compiler or @ghatana/model-extraction should host inventory scanning, graph construction, extractors for various languages and domains, synthesis, merge and diagnostics.
Recommended Phased Plan
Phase 0: Canonical Model Design – define ArtifactRecord, ArtifactGraph, SemanticProductModel and schemas for provenance, confidence and residuals.
Phase 1: TypeScript/Storybook/Prisma/State MVP – implement TS/TSX extraction using the compiler API; Storybook CSF and MCP extraction; Prisma introspection; basic state store extraction; token normalization aligned with the 2025.10 spec. Introduce Tree‑sitter incremental parsing and a persistent knowledge graph.
Phase 2: Page and Layout Extraction – add route and layout extraction, auth detection, API dependency mapping and incremental merge.
Phase 3: Style Normalization – integrate PostCSS for CSS and CSS‑in‑JS parsing; mine token candidates; use design tokens spec for normalization; record residual styles.
Phase 4: Java and SQL Deep Extraction – integrate JavaParser/OpenRewrite for Java LSTs; use SQLGlot for SQL migrations; extract services, domain models, caches, messaging and scheduled jobs.
Phase 5: Full Round‑Trip Merge – enable repository scanning, extraction into semantic models, review of low‑confidence findings, regeneration of selected slices and semantic diff/merge back into the repository. Extract build and CI/CD workflows and scripts.
