SemanticProductModel Persistence

A robust persistence strategy is critical for enabling incremental updates, versioning and cross‑repo sharing of the SemanticProductModel:

Storage architecture: use PostgreSQL with JSONB for model nodes and edges; store large artifacts (source files, residuals) in object storage. Provide a GraphQL API for graph traversal and filtering. Persist the knowledge graph built from Tree‑sitter parse trees.
Versioning: maintain append‑only snapshots for each extraction. Use semantic diffs to store deltas and support branching for experimental extractions. Provide rollback capabilities.
Incremental updates: integrate with file system watchers or git hooks; re‑extract only changed artifacts and propagate confidence scores. Merge updates into the existing model with conflict resolution.
Query and retrieval: allow graph traversal, provenance filtering, confidence thresholding and residual inspection. Provide search tools for developers and AI agents.
Export/import: support JSON/YAML export, schema validation on import, cross‑repo sharing and template libraries for reusable patterns.
Conclusion

Building a reverse compiler is a complex but transformative endeavor. The original report identified the need for a loss‑aware ArtifactGraph and a normalized SemanticProductModel. Subsequent research emphasises incremental, cross‑language parsing, knowledge graphs and adherence to stable standards like the 2025.10 design tokens spec and OpenAPI 3.2.0. By incorporating Lossless Semantic Trees, Storybook 10.3 features, SQL canonicalization and persistent knowledge graphs, Ghatana can become a migration and modernization platform capable of ingesting existing products, extracting rich models and regenerating code with confidence and provenance.